                                                      DOM(Document Object Model) Manupulation
document.getElementById('title')
document.getElementById('title').id
document.getElementById('title').className
document.getElementById('title').getAttribute('id');
document.getElementById('title').getAttribute('class');
document.getElementById('title').setAttribute('class','name');  //ovrides previos attribute
let title = document.getElementById('title');
title.style.backgroundColor = "red";
title.style.color = "white";
title.style.padding = "20px";
title.textContent //'DOM learning'

innerText gives a values which are visible on a page
textContent gives a value which are hidden as weel
innerHTML give a html element as well as content

